		<td><b>Was ARM originally cheaper than 68000?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I saw a video on YouTube from computerphile, where one of the guys who invented the ARM cpu said back in 1986 their CPU was cheaper than the 68000 and the 80368 because of the RISC architecture.  If this is the case, what took them so long to catch on?  Was ARM unavailable in Japan at the time?  Did the 32 bit data bus require too much external circuitry?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


